Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Chapter 7  -  Section 7.6", "Title",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[TextData[{
  "I",
  StyleBox["n this ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  StyleBox[" notebook, you find the solution to a system of differential \
equations with complex eigenvalues and eigenvectors. ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  StyleBox["The solution to the system will be plotted in the phase plane \
together with the direction field for the system. ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  "\n\n",
  StyleBox["In most cases, to adapt this code to other problems, you will \
have to change only the input shown in red. To open a cell grouping, \
double-click on the right-hand side of the double cell marker.",
    FontSize->14]
}], "Subsubtitle",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
  "Problem 4:   x' = ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      FormBox[
        RowBox[{"(", GridBox[{
              {"2", \(-\(5\/2\)\)},
              {\(9\/5\), \(-1\)}
              }], ")"}], TraditionalForm]]],
  " x"
}], "Section",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Finding the Eigenvalues and Corresponding Eigenvectors for the Coefficient \
Matrix\
\>", "Subsection",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Using the Formulas", "Subsubsection",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We can determine the eigenvalues for the coefficient matrix (A) by setting \
the determinant of (A - r I) equal to zero and solving for r. We will call \
upon the ",
  StyleBox["IdentityMatrix",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " function and also the determinant (",
  StyleBox["Det",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  ") function."
}], "Text",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[BoxData[{\(Clear[A, r, x, t]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"A", "=", 
        RowBox[{"(", GridBox[{
              {
                StyleBox["2",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox[\(\(-5\)\/2\),
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]},
              {
                StyleBox[\(9\/5\),
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox[\(-1\),
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}
              }], ")"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(matr = 
      A - r\ IdentityMatrix[2] // 
        Simplify\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(eigsoln = 
      Solve[Det[matr] \[Equal] 0, r]\)}], "Input",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell["\<\
Then to find the corresponding eigenvectors, we can solve the following \
system of equations. Matrix multiplication requires the use of a period, \
\".\". Without that symbol, the proper multiplication will not occur.\
\>", "Text",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[BoxData[{
    \(v1soln = 
      Solve[\((matr /. 
                r \[Rule] 
                  eigsoln[\([1, 1, 2]\)])\) . {\[Xi]1, \[Xi]2} \[Equal] {0, 
            0}, {\[Xi]1, \[Xi]2}]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    \(v2soln = 
      Solve[\((matr /. 
                r \[Rule] 
                  eigsoln[\([2, 1, 2]\)])\) . {\[Xi]1, \[Xi]2} \[Equal] {0, 
            0}, {\[Xi]1, \[Xi]2}]\)}], "Input",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell["\<\
We will get a real valued solution from the first eigenvalue and \
corresponding eigenvector in what is to follow.\
\>", "Text",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
  "Using ",
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  " Built-in Commands"
}], "Subsubsection",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[TextData[{
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  " is great at determining eigenvalues and eigenvectors. We will use the ",
  StyleBox["Eigensystem",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command here and express the result in matrix form for clarity."
}], "Text",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[BoxData[{
    \(eigs = Eigensystem[A]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    \(eigs // MatrixForm\)}], "Input",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth]
}, Closed]]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Solving the System of Differential Equations", "Subsection",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Using the Eigenvalues and Eigenvectors", "Subsubsection",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We can call upon our eigensystem results and insert the appropriate values \
to form our general solution. We will do this in two steps. The ",
  StyleBox["ComplexExpand",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command is necessary here if we wish to see our solution in real form."
}], "Text",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[BoxData[{
    \(Clear[c1, c2]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    \(soln1 = 
      eigs[\([2, 1]\)]\ \[ExponentialE]\^\(eigs[\([1, 1]\)]\ t\) // 
        ComplexExpand\)}], "Input",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell["\<\
To get the general solution, we need to separate out the real part and the \
imaginary part, each of which will form a solution. In some expressions you \
may need to pull out different parts to get the general solution.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    \(\(genlsoln = 
        c1 {\((soln1[\([1, 1]\)] + soln1[\([1, 2]\)])\), 
                soln1[\([2, 1]\)]} + \((c2/\[ImaginaryI]\ )\) {soln1[\([1, 
                    3]\)], soln1[\([2, 2]\)]} // 
          Simplify;\)\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    \(genlsoln // MatrixForm\)}], "Input"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Using the DSolve Command", "Subsubsection",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[TextData[{
  "The ",
  StyleBox["DSolve",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command is used to solve systems of differential equations in a manner \
similar to solving single differential equations, but you need to use the ",
  StyleBox["Thread",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command inside the ",
  StyleBox["DSolve",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command if we want to leave the system of equations in matrix form. Note \
that we also need the \".\" for matrix multiplication and both dependent \
variables must be called upon as functions of the independent variable, ",
  StyleBox["t",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  "..\nAs above, the ",
  StyleBox["ComplexExpand",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command is necessary here if we wish to see our solution in real form."
}], "Text",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell[BoxData[{
    \(Clear[x1, x2, t]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    \(fastsoln = \(DSolve[
            Thread[{\(x1'\)[t], \(x2'\)[t]} == A . {x1[t], x2[t]}], {x1[t], 
              x2[t]}, t] // FullSimplify\) // ComplexExpand\)}], "Input",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth],

Cell["\<\
The form of the expressions looks a bit different, but upon inspection, you \
can see that both solutions agree with the earlier result arrived at using \
eigenvalues and eigenvectors.\
\>", "Text",
  PageWidth->WindowWidth]
}, Closed]]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Plotting the Direction Field and Selected Solution Trajectories\
\>", "Subsection"],

Cell["\<\
To plot the direction field, we need to load a graphics package.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    \(<< Graphics`PlotField`\)], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
The plot of the direction field uses the right hand side of the first \
differential equation as the first input and the right hand side of the \
second differential equation as the second input. The ScaleFunction is a \
built-in option that displays the direction field well here.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"rhs1", "=", 
        RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox["2",
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
            StyleBox[" ",
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
            StyleBox["x1",
              FontColor->GrayLevel[0]]}], 
          StyleBox[" ",
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
          StyleBox["-",
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
          StyleBox[" ",
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox[\(5/2\),
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
            StyleBox[" ",
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
            StyleBox["x2",
              FontColor->GrayLevel[0]]}]}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"rhs2", "=", 
        RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox[\(9/5\),
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
            StyleBox[" ",
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
            StyleBox["x1",
              FontColor->GrayLevel[0]]}], 
          StyleBox["  ",
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
          StyleBox["-",
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
          StyleBox[" ",
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
          RowBox[{
            StyleBox["1",
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
            StyleBox[" ",
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
            StyleBox["x2",
              FontColor->GrayLevel[0]]}]}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"plotvf", "=", 
        RowBox[{"PlotVectorField", "[", 
          RowBox[{\({rhs1, rhs2}\), ",", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
              RowBox[{"x1", ",", 
                StyleBox[\(-30\),
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox[",",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox["30",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "}"}], ",", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
              RowBox[{"x2", ",", 
                StyleBox[\(-30\),
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox[",",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox["30",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "}"}], 
            ",", \(ScaleFunction \[Rule] \(( .4 &)\)\), 
            ",", \(AspectRatio \[Rule] 1\)}], "]"}]}], ";"}]}], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We will call upon the general solution formulated using the eigenvalues \
and eigenvectors and evaluate that solution for a set of values of the \
arbitrary constants. Keep in mind that since the real portion of the \
eigenvalues was positive, the coefficient of t in the ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(TraditionalForm\`\[ExponentialE]\^at\)]],
  "expression is positive. Hence all solutions will spiral out at t \[Rule] \
\[Infinity]."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    \(functionarray = 
      Table[genlsoln /. {c1 \[Rule] i, c2 \[Rule] j}, {i, \(-20\), 20, 
          5}, {j, \(-20\), 20, 5}]\)], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "Now, we will use the ",
  StyleBox["ParametricPlot ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  "command to plot the solutions, but, because both of the solutions get very \
large, we will limit the window for the plot."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"plotsoln", "=", 
        RowBox[{"ParametricPlot", "[", 
          RowBox[{\(Evaluate[functionarray[\([1]\)]]\), ",", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
              RowBox[{"t", ",", 
                StyleBox[\(-10\),
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox[",",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox["10",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "}"}], ",", 
            RowBox[{"PlotRange", "\[Rule]", 
              RowBox[{"{", 
                StyleBox[\({\(-30\), 30}, {\(-30\), 30}\),
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "}"}]}], 
            ",", \(PlotStyle \[Rule] RGBColor[1, 0, 0]\)}], "]"}]}], 
      ";"}]], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "Now, we can plot these together. If they do not match, we have made a \
mistake. The limitation expressed in ",
  StyleBox["PlotRange",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " is necessary here as well."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Show", "[", 
        RowBox[{"plotvf", ",", "plotsoln", ",", 
          RowBox[{"PlotRange", "\[Rule]", 
            RowBox[{
              StyleBox["{",
                FontColor->GrayLevel[0]], 
              StyleBox[\({\(-30\), 30}, {\(-30\), 30}\),
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "}"}]}]}], "]"}], 
      ";"}]], "Input"]
}, Closed]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
